scene_description: the background is made of blue pixels. green pixels outline the grid and form shapes and lines inside of it. there is a red square of 16 pixels near the bottom right of the grid and a black square of 16 pixels on the left side of the grid.
literal_instruction: replace all of the black pixels in the grid with blue pixels. make a new square of 16 black pixels; the top of the black square will be in the 2nd row from the top of the grid and extend from the 5th column from the left to the 9th column from the left. the base of the square is in the same columns but is 3 rows lower than the top of the square. the square of black pixels should not encroach on any of the green pixels and should be fully filled,
